Every resident of Kalmykia is a debtor
Residents of the Republic increasingly visit the official Internet site of the Office of the Federal Bailiff Service of Russia for the Republic of Kazakhstan.
According to the specialists of the Department of Organizational and Control Work, Informatization and Information Security of the Republican Agency, over the past eight months, more than 140 thousand visits to the site itself have been registered, more than 42 thousand - to the section "Data Bank of Execution Proceedings", and 661 payment receipts for payment of debts have been downloaded.
According to Valery Bogdanov, Chairman of the Public Council under the UFSSP of Russia for the Republic of Kazakhstan, virtually every resident of the region has debts for utility payments, traffic police fines, bank loans, loans, and no one is insured against unforeseen situations.
But debtors may face negative consequences in the form of, for example, a travel ban.
That is why the UFSSP of Russia for the Republic of Kazakhstan recommends that anyone who has planned a trip abroad should check with the department of bailiffs at their place of residence or on the website www.r08fssprus.ru for information about the presence of unpaid debts and pay them off.
The Service has created a "Data Bank of enforcement proceedings" for the convenience of citizens.
This special electronic application is available not only on the regional sites of the UFSSP of Russia, but also in social networks and means of mobile communication iPad, iPhone and smartphone.
The data bank contains information about enforcement proceedings initiated by Kalmyk bailiffs against all debtors, explains Delgir Bodgaeva, Assistant Head of the UFSSP of Russia for the Republic of Kazakhstan.
"In case of arrears, the system displays information about the number and date of initiation of enforcement proceedings; the name of the authority that issued the enforcement order or other act; its numbers, amount and type of debt; the address of the bailiff's department; the name of the bailiff; the contact phone number.
Information on the progress of enforcement proceedings can also be obtained on the portal of public services at: http: / / epgu.gosuslugi.ru "
