The Ministry of Finance of the Russian Federation has forecast the ruble exchange rate for 17 years ahead
The Ministry of Finance of Russia expects a gradual weakening of the ruble exchange rate - up to 73.9 roubles per dollar by 2031-2035, follows from the draft long-term budget forecast submitted to the State Duma together with the draft federal budget.
In 2021-2025, the ruble exchange rate is forecast to be 66.4 roubles to the dollar, in 2026-2030 - 71.1 roubles, and in the next five years - 73.9.
The agency notes that these figures are the nominal rate.
The real effective rate (an indicator that takes into account changes in the exchange rates of countries that are the main trading partners of the Russian Federation) will remain stable, officials assure.
As for inflation, until 2020 it will be 3.5%, and then it will stabilize at about 4%, the Ministry of Finance believes.
